ğŸ”¹ Why Post-Mauryan Period is Important?

After the decline of the Mauryas (2nd century BCE), India saw:

Political decentralisation

Rise of regional powers

Foreign interactions

Growth of trade, coins, art, and religion

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Focus:
Contributions of dynasties + cultural & economic developments.

ğŸ”µ Shunga Dynasty
Founder

Pushyamitra Shunga

Key Points

Capital: Pataliputra

Brahmanical revival

Performed Ashvamedha Yajna

Patronage to art (Bharhut Stupa)

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Trap:
Shungas did not destroy Buddhism completely â€” both co-existed.

ğŸŸ  Satavahana Dynasty (Deccan)
Founder

Simuka

Important Ruler

Gautamiputra Satakarni

Key Features

Controlled Deccan trade routes

Issued lead coins

Patronised Buddhism

Matrilineal traces (names after mother)

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Focus:
Satavahanas = bridge between north & south India.

ğŸ”´ Kushana Dynasty
Founder

Kujula Kadphises

Greatest Ruler

Kanishka

Capital

Purushapura (Peshawar)

Key Contributions

Patron of Buddhism (Mahayana)

Fourth Buddhist Council

Introduced gold coins

Gandhara & Mathura art flourished

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Favourite:
Kanishka + Mahayana Buddhism + Gandhara art.

ğŸ”¹ Cultural & Economic Developments

Growth of urban centres

Expansion of Silk Route trade

Use of coins increased

Sanskrit & Prakrit both flourished

